data.title: Sports awards: Dagg looks strong awards contender
data.meta_description: Kiwi rugby league legend Stacey Jones and retired Silver Ferns netballer Temepara George will be the guest speakers at the Ngati Kahungunu Sportsperson of...
data.text:
All Black, Crusaders and Magpies stars Israel Dagg and Zac Guildford are joined by retired Breakers basketballer Paul Henare and Under-20 World Cup footballer Dakota Lucas as the finalists in this category.

Taking his form for the All Blacks into account during the year ending September 30, Dagg must rate as the favourite and should he win this category he'll be the hot favourite for the premier award.

Henare is also a finalist for the coach award and considering his work at international level and second placing in his first season in charge of the Hawks he must be regarded as the favourite in this category.

Guildford and 10-time national softball champion as a coach, Tom Makea snr, are former premier award winners among the finalists again.

Touch referee Zarne Johnson, who is a multiple winner of the official award, is the hot favourite again after his stint at the world championships in Scotland this year.

Tickets for the function went on sale this morning.

FINALISTS

Junior Sportsman: Matthew Bird (basketball), Hone-Paora Hoepo-Scott (swimming), Horowai Puketapu (softball), Eli Raheke (shearing).

Junior Sportswoman: Aaliyah Ah Kiong (basketball), Courtney Gettins (softball), Rita Hokianga (softball), Tiffany Piper (shooting).

Official: Suzie Hiha (basketball), Zane Johnson (touch), Zarne Johnson (touch), Danielle Maulder (netball).

Coach: Anaru Bartlett (rugby league and touch), Paul Henare (basketball), Tom Makea snr (softball), Kevin Tamati (rugby league).

Active Kaumatua: Elliott Hawea (basketball), Waiora Rogers (triathlon), Tanira Te Au (rugby, Triathlon), Kevin Tamati (rugby league).

Administrator: Anaru Bartlett (rugby league and touch), Anthony Morley (rugby), Heather Skipworth (IronMaori), Conrad Waitoa (rugby).

Senior Sportswoman: Candis Cardie (touch), Jordan Hunter (basketball), Roni Nuku (waka ama).

Senior Sportsman: Israel Dagg (rugby), Zac Guildford (rugby), Paul Henare (basketball), Dakota Lucas (football).
